03/11/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Senior officials and international specialists launched roundtable discussions about corporate governance at Sarajevo University on Monday (3 November). 
The forum will review management of public companies and will propose measures to fight corruption. 
BiH officials are also expected to tackle ongoing reforms in the indirect taxation system.
In other news, Osman Topcagic, chairman of the BiH Office for European Integration, said Sunday that the EU would release a report on implementation of the Stabilisation and Association Agreement in BiH by the end of the month. 
The study will cover 365 reform benchmarks linked to the economic and political situation. 
(Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz, Oslobodjenje - 03/11/03; BHTV 1 - 02/11/03)
